xj2RXZfyc2aoz3HdrERMZ37c.text: This library provides a simple data store for survey apps. It records a name and a vote (as a number). Each vote also contains a timestamp and a location.

cPJRu5H8wytGmk34R4j3TbtI.text: Call the `initialize` action to start a new survey.

IRzXSW94lXtzuJxZuOg0NUHU.text: Call the 'set vote' action to record a new vote. Each participant may only provide one vote so the `name` is used as a key.

FCIvR9bmskQqM2fVo5A7tp6a.text: By default, the acceptable range of votes is 0 to 5 included. You can change that using the `set vote range` action.

xH6pdJD5Z3m44OYn2hQ4hkoD.text: Specifies the acceptable range for the votes. Any vote outside this range will be clamped. Default is 1 to 5 included.

EBJrxOQ2Zdk1sc5X7hUeSEQv.text: The library provides `sum` and `average` actions to easily gather the overall data.

EKJzTP37sRjopCMmwC5V4Cwd.text: The result can also be added to a map using the 'map votes' action.

s4Okd4ZrJEFn6hhNfYdZb7ax.text: Computes the histogram of votes, i.e. the number of votes for each entry.

cgjbS5kI4AcC4o4LxZoNXEnF.text: You can easily retrieve the histogram of votes and display it as a chart using the `histogram` action.
